<Project Sdk="Microsoft.NET.Sdk">

  <PropertyGroup>
    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>
    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>
    <ImplicitUsings>enable</ImplicitUsings>
    <Nullable>enable</Nullable>
    <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>
    <ToolCommandName>microkit</ToolCommandName>
    <PackageId>MicroserviceKit</PackageId>
    <Version>0.4.3</Version>
    <Authors>Paweł Pilichowski</Authors>
    <Description>🚀 Complete toolkit for generating production-ready .NET 8 microservices with DDD, CQRS, Clean Architecture, Event-Driven Architecture, and comprehensive infrastructure. Generate enterprise-grade microservices with REST APIs, CQRS, MongoDB read models, RabbitMQ messaging, external service integration, Docker, and complete testing suite.</Description>
    <PackageTags>microservices;toolkit;generator;ddd;cqrs;dotnet;clean-architecture;rest-api;event-driven;mongodb;rabbitmq;docker;enterprise;microkit</PackageTags>
    <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>
    <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/suranig/microservice-net8-ddd</PackageProjectUrl>
    <RepositoryUrl>https://github.com/suranig/microservice-net8-ddd</RepositoryUrl>
    <RepositoryType>git</RepositoryType>
    <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>
    <PackageReleaseNotes>
🎉 Release 0.4.3 - Critical Bug Fixes!

🐛 CRITICAL BUGS FIXED:
- ✅ Fixed case mismatch in command parameter access (command.id → command.Id)
- ✅ Replaced incorrect _bus.InvokeAsync() with proper MassTransit CreateRequestClient pattern
- ✅ Added missing response logic for Update and Delete commands (await context.RespondAsync)
- ✅ Added MediatR package reference to ApplicationModule for proper compilation

🏗️ COMPILATION IMPROVEMENTS:
- ✅ Domain layer: 0 errors, 0 warnings
- ✅ Application layer: 0 errors, 0 warnings  
- ✅ Infrastructure layer: 0 errors, 0 warnings
- ✅ All enterprise templates now generate properly compiling code

🚀 PRODUCTION READY: All major compilation issues resolved for enterprise microservices!

Previous 0.4.2 features:
- ✅ Complete Docker &amp; Makefile support for all enterprise templates
- ✅ Fixed DockerModule configuration structure
- ✅ Templates generate 64 files with full containerization
    </PackageReleaseNotes>
  </PropertyGroup>

  <ItemGroup>
    <PackageReference Include="System.CommandLine" Version="2.0.0-beta4.22272.1" />
